#use wml::debian::template title="Submit Mirror Information"

If you would like to submit information about a mirror of Debian
(ftp archive, web, Incoming), you can do that using this form.

<form method=post action="http://cgi.debian.org/cgi-bin/submit_mirror.pl">

<define-tag window>\
	<strong>%0: </strong>\
	<input type="text" name="%1" size="%2"><br>
</define-tag>

<window Site site 30>
# <window type type 60>
<STRONG>Aliases: </STRONG> (comma separated list)
<input type="text" name="aliases" size="60"><br>

<H3>Types of mirrors and methods of accessing them (leave
non-relevant fields blank):</H3>
<ul>
<li><window "HTTP access to archive"   archive-http   30>
<li><window "FTP access to archive"    archive-ftp    30>
<li><window "RSYNC access to archive"  archive-rsync  30>
<li><window "HTTP access to non-US"    nonus-http     30>
<li><window "FTP access to non-US"     nonus-ftp      30>
<li><window "RSYNC access to non-US"   nonus-rsync    30>
<li><window "HTTP access to Incoming"  incoming-http  30>
<li><window "FTP access to Incoming"   incoming-ftp   30>
<li><window "HTTP access to www"       www-http       30>
<li><window "RSYNC access to www"      www-rsync      30>
</ul>

<H3>Information about the mirror site</H3>
<window "Mirrors from"             mirrors_from  30>
<window "Name of site maintainer"  maint_name    30>
<window "Email of site maintainer" maint_email   30>
<window "Location of site"         location      30>
<window "Name of site sponsor"     sponsor_name  30>
<window "URL of site sponsor"      sponsor_url   30>
Note: if more than one sponsor, add the others in the comment
below and they will be added by hand.<br>
<STRONG>Comment:</STRONG>
<textarea name="comment" cols=40 rows=7 maxlength=256 wrap=virtual></textarea><br>

<INPUT TYPE="SUBMIT"> <INPUT TYPE="RESET">
</form>

